Laparoscopy in the investigation of infertility. Gynaecological units in Great Britain are using the laparoscope increasingly frequently to investigate the infertile woman in this paper the need for this form of investigation is emphasized. In the Professorial Unit at Glasgow Royral Infirmary, the findings (over a three years period), obtained by the laparoscopic investigation of the infertile woman, are given. It is found that laparoscopy frequently identifies a possible cause of infertility in women whose failure to conceive has remained unexplained by other methods of investigation.